@node LI_PLAIN - Plain Data Structures
@subsection LI_PLAIN - Plain Data Structures

@node ll_hdioc Structure
@subsubsection ll_hdioc Structure

The @type{ll_hdioc} structure is formatted as follows:

@example
@group
struct ll_hdioc @{
    uint8_t lli_type;
    uint8_t lli_spare[3];
    uint32_t lli_snid;
@};
@end group
@end example

The @type{ll_hdioc} structure contains the following members:

@table @member
@item lli_type
Always @pval{LLI_PLAIN}.
@item lli_spare
Spare bytes for alignment: set to zero by issuer and ignored by responder.
@item lli_snid
Specifies the subnetwork identifier (link identifier) for the operation.
@end table

@node LI_SNID - Subnetwork Identifier Data Strucures
@subsection LI_SNID - Subnetwork Identifier Data Strucures

@node ll_snioc Structure
@subsubsection ll_snioc Structure

The @type{ll_snioc} structure is used in the @pioc{L_SETSNID}, @pioc{L_GETSNID},
@pioc{M_SETSNID} and @pioc{M_GETSNID} input-output controls.

The @type{ll_snioc} structure is formatted as follows:

@example
@group
struct ll_snioc @{
    uint8_t lli_type;
    uint8_t lli_class;
    uint8_t lli_spare[2];
    uint32_t lli_snid;
    uint32_t lli_index;
    uint32_t lli_slp_snid;
    uint16_t lli_slp_pri;
@};
@end group
@end example

The @type{ll_snioc} structure contains the following members:

@table @member
@item lli_type
Always @pval{LLI_SNID}.
@item lli_class
Specifies the class of the link being registered.  This field can be one of the
following values:
@multitable @columnfractions .2 .8
@item @pval{LC_LLC1} @tab LLC Type 1 link.
@item @pval{LC_LLC2} @tab LLC TYpe 2 link.
@item @pval{LC_LAPBDTE} @tab LAPB DTE.
@item @pval{LC_LAPBXDTE} @tab LAPB DTE with extended addressing.
@item @pval{LC_LAPBDCE} @tab LAPB DCE.
@item @pval{LC_LAPBXDCE} @tab LAPB DCE with extended addressing.
@item @pval{LC_LAPDTE} @tab LAP DTE.
@item @pval{LC_LAPDCE} @tab LAP DCE.
@item @pval{LC_HDLC} @tab HDLC.
@item @pval{LC_HDLCX} @tab HDLC with extended addressing.
@item @pval{LC_MLAPBDTE} @tab LAPB DTE multilink.
@item @pval{LC_MLAPBXDTE} @tab LAPB DTE multilink with extended addressing.
@item @pval{LC_MLAPBDCE} @tab LAPB DCE multilink.
@item @pval{LC_MLAPBXDCE} @tab LAPB DCE multilink with extended addressing.
@item @pval{LC_MLP} @tab MLP link.
@end multitable
@item lli_spare
Spare bytes for alignment: set to zero by issuer and ignored by responder.
@item lli_snid
Specifies the subnetwork identifier (link identifier) for the operation.
@item lli_index
Specifies the lower multiplex identifier of the Stream linked under a
multiplexing driver as returned from @command{I_LINK(7)}.@footnote{See the
@manref{I_LINK(7)} manual page.}
@item lli_slp_snid
Specifies the subnetwork (link) identifier for an SLP link within an MLP link.
@item lli_slp_pri
Specifies the subnetwork (link) priority within an MLP link.
@end table

