@node hdlc Driver
@section hdlc Driver

The @file{hdlc} driver is a pseudo-device @cite{STREAMS} driver that provides
raw HDLC framing as specified in @cite{ISO/IEC 3309} described in reference
@ref{ISO3309,,ISO3309}.

The @file{hdlc} driver provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper multiplex service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{hdlc} driver is documented in the @manref{hdlc(4)} manual page.

@node lapb Driver
@section lapb Driver

The @file{lapb} driver is a pseudo-device @cite{STREAMS} driver that provides
the X.25 compatible LAPB procedures as specified in @cite{ISO/IEC 7776}
described in reference @ref{ISO7776,,ISO7776}.
This driver, in combination with the @file{x25} multiplexing driver, provides
X.25 over LAPB as described in reference @ref{ISO8208,,ISO8208}.

The @file{lapb} driver provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper multiplex service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{lapb} driver is documented in the @manref{lapb(4)} manual page.

@node llc1 Driver
@section llc1 Driver

The @file{llc1} driver is a pseudo-device @cite{STREAMS} driver that provides
the IEEE 802.2 LLC Type 1 (LLC1) procedures as specified in @cite{ISO/IEC
8802-2} described in reference @ref{ISO8802-2,,ISO8802-2}.
This driver, in combination with the @file{x25} multiplexing driver, provides
X.25 over LLC1 as described in refeference @ref{ISO8881,,ISO8881}.

The @file{llc1} driver provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper multiplex service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{llc1} driver is documented in the @manref{llc1(4)} manual page.

@node llc2 Driver
@section llc2 Driver

The @file{llc1} driver is a pseudo-device @cite{STREAMS} driver that provides
the IEEE 802.2 LLC Type 2 (LLC2) procedures as specified in @cite{ISO/IEC
8802-2} described in reference @ref{ISO8802-2,,ISO8802-2}.
This driver, in combination with the @file{x25} multiplexing driver, provides
X.25 over LLC2 as described in refeference @ref{ISO8881,,ISO8881}.

The @file{llc2} driver provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper multiplex service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{llc2} driver is documented in the @manref{llc2(4)} manual page.

@node s_llic Module
@section s_llic Module

The @file{s_llic} module is a pushable @cite{STREAMS} module that converts
between the LLI input-output controls described in this manual and the DLPI
input-output controls used by the @url{http://www.openss7.org/,OpenSS7 Project}.
This particular module does not convert primitives, as both the LLI and the DLPI
use the primitives of the @cite{Data Link Provider Interface, Revision
2.0.0} described in reference @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{s_llic} module provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper and lower service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{s_llic} module is documented in the @manref{s_llic(4)} manual page.

@node s_lli Module
@section s_lli Module

The @file{s_lli} module is a pushable @cite{STREAMS} module that converts
between the LLI input-output controls described in this manual and the DLPI
input-output controls used by the @url{http://www.openss7.org/,OpenSS7 Project}.
This particular module converts between the LLI primitives described in this
manual and the primitives of the @cite{Data Link Provider Interface}, described
in reference @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{s_llic} module provides a @cite{Data Link Provider Interface} as its
upper and lower service interface, as described in @ref{DLPI,,DLPI}.

The @file{s_lli} module is documented in the @manref{s_lli(4)} manual page.

